New recipe: Vegan split pea soup. This is the silkiest, creamiest split pea soup ... super easy to make! 🌱

Ingredients
1 cup raw cashews, soaked in plenty of water for a few hours or overnight, then drained
1 tsp apple cider vinegar
a few pinches of flaky sea salt
1 cup water
1 TB olive oil
1 large white onion, chopped
1/4 tsp salt
1 tsp dried thyme
4–6 cloves garlic, minced
1 TB vegan butter
1/4 tsp liquid smoke
1 1/2 cup split green peas, picked over and rinsed
3 tsp vegan bouillon, whisked and dissolved into 2 cups hot water
4 cups water

Search "vegan split pea soup" on the blog or dm me for the recipe! ✌️

So in love with this little bub. 🥰

I LOVE this vegan chicken and rice recipe! Sage, thyme, rosemary and marjoram are combined with sauteed vegetables and broth to create an amazing taste and aroma.

Seasoned soy curls are added for vegan protein and rice for heartiness. This recipe is super non-fussy and can be adapted to your liking. Sub noodles for rice or leave out the carbs completely. 

Sub commercially prepared vegan chicken for soy curls and add a little miso if you want a little extra umami. If you are feeling sick, adding miso will make you feel better, at least it does for me. 

We have been loving variations of this soup for weeknight dinners, and hope you will too!

.

.

.

Every fall, I love the ritual of making my first batch of homemade ravioli. 🍃🍂🍁

I roll out and fill tons of it to store in the freezer for carby dinners throughout the month. 

I love filling it with homemade cashew cheese, @kitehillfoods ricotta, or @fieldroast Italian sausage. Pumpkin-sage ravioli and mushroom ravioli are delicious, too! 😋 

Search for "how to make homemade ravioli" on the blog for a step-by-step tutorial! 🥰

Celebrate the magic of the holiday season with a twist on tradition with this vegan blueberry-blackberry cobbler.✨🎄🍓🫐

While berry cobblers usually transport us to summer sun, this version brings on winter coziness with its jammy mixed berries and buttery crust.❄️🥧

Not only does it add a burst of color to your Christmas table, but also an unexpected surprise next to pumpkin or sweet potato pies. 🍂✨ 

And the best part? This cobbler is as easy as pie! 🌟✨ 

#vegan #veganaf #vegancommunity #veganholiday #veganfood #veganrecipes #vegansofinstagram #vegansofig #vegansofinsta #veganfoodporn #vegandessert

✨ Vegan Wellington ✨

This season, add a show-stopping Vegan Wellington to your holiday table! 🌿✨ Wrapped in flaky, buttery vegan puff pastry, this Wellington uses @fieldroast apple-sage sausage, hearty lentils, and aromatic herbs like sage and thyme, all wrapped up in a savory mushroom duxelles. 🍏🍄✨

This three-part centerpiece is fun to make as it is delicious! From the flavorful filling to the umami-rich duxelles and the golden perfection of braided puff pastry, it’s a holiday masterpiece that’s sure to impress. 🎄🍽️

Swipe left for a sneak peek at the making of this vegan dish! 👉✨

👩‍🍳 Cooking Tips:

☑️ Prep your ingredients in advance for a seamless cooking process.
☑️Use vegan butter and puff pastry for a totally plant-based dish. Most puff pastry is already vegan, just scan the ingredient list!
☑️ Enjoy with mashed potatoes, gravy, and your favorite holiday sides for the perfect festive feast! 🥔🍴

🌱 Vegan Wellington Recipe: https://olivesfordinner.com/vegan-wellington/
